  "doc_id": "48452",
  "text": "The lack of specificity among the pharmacological tools used to activate and inhibit AMPK presents a challenge for determining whether their effects are due to AMPK or some other off-target effect. Most known AMPK activating drugs have substantial AMPK-independent effects [CITATION_1] . For instance, at high concentrations AICAR can induce apoptosis via an AMPK-independent mechanism [178] . The selectivity of AMPK inhibitors is also problematic. The most frequently used small molecule inhibitor of AMPK, compound C, potently inhibits other kinases and has numerous AMPK-independent effects, including antiproliferative effects and cytotoxicity [CITATION_2] . Thus, conclusions about the effects of AMPK based on these modulators must be considered with caution. There is a significant need to develop more targeted approaches to manipulate AMPK activity, both for research purposes and as potential therapeutics.",
